prompt
prompt =========================================================================
prompt SECTION 19 - EVENT-SPECIFIC POINTERS
prompt =========================================================================

select
    trim('&&p_wait_event') as event,
    case
        when trim('&&p_wait_event') = '-' then 'No event drilldown requested.'
        when lower(trim('&&p_wait_event')) = 'db file sequential read' then
            'Single-block reads. Usually index-driven access, random I/O, hot index/table probes, or nested-loop amplification. Check top objects and event plan lines.'
        when lower(trim('&&p_wait_event')) = 'db file scattered read' then
            'Multiblock reads. Usually full scans or index fast full scans. Check pruning, scan size, and whether the chosen plan line is doing too much scanning.'
        when lower(trim('&&p_wait_event')) in ('direct path read temp','direct path write temp') then
            'Temp spill. Usually sort/hash spill or workarea pressure. Check join cardinality, hash/sort plan lines, and whether PX amplified temp usage.'
        when lower(trim('&&p_wait_event')) in ('gc buffer busy acquire','gc current block busy','gc cr block busy') then
            'RAC hot block or cross-instance block contention. Check instance skew, hot objects, service placement, and event concentration on specific plan lines.'
        when lower(trim('&&p_wait_event')) = 'read by other session' then
            'Many sessions waiting for blocks another session is already reading. Check duplicated probes/scans, hot objects, and whether one access path is driving the pile-up.'
        when lower(trim('&&p_wait_event')) = 'enq: tx - row lock contention' then
            'Row lock contention. Check blocker signatures, app commit behavior, hot rows, and whether a small set of objects dominates the event.'
        when lower(trim('&&p_wait_event')) = 'resmgr:cpu quantum' then
            'CPU throttling or heavy CPU pressure. Check concurrency, Resource Manager policy, and whether the SQL is being rationed rather than intrinsically slow.'
        when lower(trim('&&p_wait_event')) in ('cursor: pin s wait on x','library cache lock','library cache: mutex x') then
            'Cursor/library cache contention. Check parse churn, child cursor growth, bind mismatch, and application cursor reuse.'
        when lower(trim('&&p_wait_event')) like 'enq:%' then
            'Enqueue wait. Check blocker signatures, object concentration, and the specific enqueue family / mode.'
        else
            'Use the event-object, event-plan-line, event-minute, and event-module sections together. The key question is whether the event is concentrated on one object, one plan step, one instance, or one app entry point.'
    end as pointer_text
from dual;

